DIGEST
SB 429 Original 2026 Regular Session Lambert
Present law provides that each owner of a motorboat, houseboat, or sailboat required to be
numbered by the state shall submit an application to the Louisiana Wildlife and Fisheries
Commission accompanied by a designated fee. Further provides for the issuance of
certificate of number and a decal.
Present law provides for applications filed with the commission in the event ownership of
a boat changes.
Proposed law retains present law.
Proposed law provides for application by the possessor of a motorboat, houseboat, or
sailboat with a certificate of number that has lapsed for at least five years.
Proposed law requires such an applicant to submit an affidavit stating a notice has been
provided by certified mail, return receipt requested, to the last holder of a certificate of
number and the applicant has been in possession of the boat for at least one year immediately
preceding the date of application.
Proposed law requires copies of the notice and return receipt be submitted with the affidavit
and all documentation be in a form prescribed by the commission.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 34:851.20(C))
